# Controllers

## Boilerplate

```csharp
[ApiController]
[Route("api/[controller]")]
public class ExampleController : ControllerBase
{
    private readonly IExampleService _service;
    private readonly ILogger<ExampleController> _logger;

    public ExampleController(IExampleService service, ILogger<ExampleController> logger)
    {
        _service = service;
        _logger = logger;
    }
}
```

- Namespace: `kingsightapi.Controllers`
- Inject `I*Service` + `ILogger<TController>` only — no `SqlConnection` in controllers
- Register new services in `Program.cs` before adding endpoints

## Routes

- Base route: `api/[controller]` (controller name drives URL, e.g. `LoansController` → `/api/loans`)
- Use explicit route templates for sub-resources: `[HttpGet("investor-details")]`, `[HttpPut("{loanKey:int}/investor-alias")]`
- Prefer `int` route constraints for numeric keys

## Request validation

Return `BadRequest` with a clear message when:

- Body is null
- Required collections are null or empty
- Required fields are missing

Do this in the controller before calling the service.

## Response conventions

| Outcome | Status |
|---------|--------|
| Success with body | `Ok(result)` |
| Update succeeded | `NoContent()` |
| Row not found | `NotFound()` |
| Client cancelled | `499` (non-standard; existing pattern) |
| Unhandled error | `500` with generic message (no exception details to client) |

## Error handling

Wrap action bodies in try/catch:

```csharp
catch (OperationCanceledException)
{
    _logger.LogInformation("… cancelled");
    return StatusCode(499);
}
catch (Exception ex)
{
    _logger.LogError(ex, "Error …");
    return StatusCode(500, "An error occurred while …");
}
```

Use structured logging placeholders (`{LoanKey}`, `{Count}`) — not string interpolation in log messages.

## Comments & readability

Every public action must have a route comment immediately above it (matches existing controllers):

```csharp
// GET: api/loans/investor-details
[HttpGet("investor-details")]
public async Task<ActionResult<List<InvestorDto>>> GetInvestorDetails()
```

Use the HTTP verb and full path (including route template segments), not just the method name.

### When to add extra comments

Add a short `//` line when the code is not self-explanatory:

- Duplicate routes for Angular (`// alias and aliases — Angular client uses plural`)
- Non-standard status codes (`// 499 — client closed request / cancellation`)
- Validation rules that mirror product wording (`// batch body must include at least one investor`)
- Group related actions with a blank line and optional section header:

```csharp
// --- Loan alias batch ---

// GET: api/loans/loanalias
```

### Controller class header (optional)

For new controllers, a one-line class comment is fine if the name alone is ambiguous:

```csharp
// Exposes mort.dim_investor read and alias batch update for the Kingsight UI.
[ApiController]
```

### What not to comment

- Constructor parameter assignments
- Standard try/catch structure (documented in this rule file)
- `return Ok(result)` when the route comment and method name already describe the action

Prefer improving `BadRequest` message text over commenting `if (request is null)`.
